  "raw_text_excerpt": "2026 MONACO GRAND PRIX\n07 - 09 June 2026\nThe FIA Formula 1 Technical Delegate\nFrom The FIA Formula 1 Technical Delegate\nTo The Stewards\nDocument 14\nDate 05 June 2026\nTime 10:28\nTitle Technical Delegate's Report\nDescription PU elements used per driver up to now\nEnclosed 06 MCO GP 26 TDR01.pdf\nManuel Leal\n\n1 \n \n \n2026 MONACO GRAND PRIX \n05 – 07 June 2026 \n \n  \n  \nFrom The FIA Formula 1 Technical Delegate   \n  \nTo The Stewards      Date  05 June 2026 \n  \n \n \nTECHNICAL DELEGATE’S REPORT \n \nThe drivers entered in the 2026 Formula One Championship have used the below listed number of \npower unit elements during this season so far: \n \nICE Internal Combustion Engine TC Turbo Charger \nEX EXHaust set MGU-K Motor Generator Unit – Kinetic \nES Energy Store unit PU-CE Power Unit Control Electronics unit \nPU-ANC Power Unit ANCillary component \n  \n \nN° Car Driver ICE TC EXH MGU \n-K \nES PU-\nCE \nPU-\nANC \n81 McLaren Mercedes Oscar Piastri 2 2 2 1 1 1 2 \n01 McLaren Mercedes Lando Norris  2 2 2 1 3 3 3 \n63 Mercedes George Russell 2 2 2 1 2 2 3 \n12 Mercedes Kimi Antonelli 2 2 2 1 2 2 3 \n03 Red Bull Racing RB Ford Max Verstappen 1 1 1 2 1 1 2 \n06 Red Bull Racing RB Ford Isack Hadjar  3  3 3 2 4 4 3 \n16 F"
